1. Proper Surface Preparation
A flawless paint job starts with a well-prepped surface. Professional painters never skip this step because even the highest-quality paint wonâ€™t cover imperfections properly.
Steps for Proper Surface Prep:
Cleaning the Surface â€“ Dirt, dust, and grease can prevent paint from adhering properly. Pros use mild soap and water or a degreaser for kitchen walls.
Sanding Rough Spots â€“ Any existing bumps, old paint drips, or rough patches are sanded smooth. For walls, fine-grit sandpaper (120-180 grit) works best.
Patching Holes and Cracks â€“ Small holes from nails or cracks in drywall are filled with spackle or joint compound and then sanded smooth once dry.
Applying Primer â€“ Priming ensures even absorption and helps paint stick better. For darker colors or stains, a high-quality primer is essential.

2. Using High-Quality Paint
Not all paints are created equal. Cheap paints often require multiple coats, dry unevenly, and are more prone to streaks. Professional painters invest in high-quality paints that have better pigments, coverage, and durability.
Key features of good paint:
High pigment concentration for better coverage
Self-leveling properties to reduce visible brush or roller marks
Appropriate sheen for the surface (e.g., matte for ceilings, eggshell for walls, satin or semi-gloss for trim)

