4. Mastering the Application Technique
Even with the best paint and tools, the wrong application can lead to streaks, roller marks, or uneven coverage. Professional painters follow specific techniques to ensure a seamless finish.
How to Apply Paint Like a Pro:
Use the "W" or "M" Technique â€“ When rolling paint, start by making a large "W" or "M" shape on the wall, then fill it in without lifting the roller too often. This prevents visible roller lines.
Maintain a Wet Edge â€“ To avoid lap marks, always keep a wet edge by overlapping slightly with each new stroke before the paint dries.
Feather Out Brush Strokes â€“ When cutting in around edges, feather out brush strokes by lightly lifting the brush at the end of each stroke.
Apply Multiple Thin Coats â€“ One thick coat of paint will likely streak or drip. Instead, apply two thin coats, allowing proper drying time between each.

5. Allowing Proper Drying Time
Rushing the job can lead to visible imperfections. Professionals follow the recommended drying times on the paint can, typically waiting at least 2-4 hours between coats for latex paint. Humidity and temperature can also affect drying, so painting in ideal conditions (between 50-85Â°F) helps prevent issues.

6. Finishing Touches for a Perfect Look
Once the paint is dry, pros do a final inspection to fix any small imperfections. They check for streaks, roller marks, or uneven spots and do minor touch-ups if needed. Some even lightly sand between coats for an ultra-smooth finish.

